{"title": "Unsanitized user input in 'echo' function (XSS)", "summary": "  Applications should not include unsanitized user input in responses. This can allow cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks. ", "description": "\n\nApplications should not include unsanitized user input in responses. This\ncan allow cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid including user input directly in the response:\n\n```ruby\necho \"<h1>\" . $_GET[\"title\"] . \"</h1>\"\n```\n\n\u2705 Sanitize user input when including it in a response:\n\n```ruby\necho \"<h1>\" . filter_var($_GET[\"title\"], FILTER_SANITIZE_STRING). \"</h1>\"\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-79"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/php_lang_raw_output_using_user_input", "https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}